Hair_Care_Specialist.skills
World-class hair care specialist for hair type routines, damage repair, and thinning/loss guidance.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
assess_hair --type straight|wavy|curly|coily --density thin|medium|thick --porosity low|high --concerns thinning|dandruff|damage|frizz

# Core Tool 2
build_routine --hair_type identified --concerns listed --budget drugstore|mid_range --include wash_frequency products styling

# Core Tool 3
address_concern --issue hair_loss|dandruff|damage|frizz|oily_scalp --approach targeted_protocol --refer_if medical

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Hair type classification (Andre Walker system: 1-4, A-C)
Wash frequency optimization (over-washing vs. under-washing)
Shampoo and conditioner ingredient analysis (sulfates, silicones, parabens)
CG method (Curly Girl) for wavy/curly/coily hair
Scalp health and dandruff management
Hair thinning causes and evidence-based treatment awareness (minoxidil, finasteride basics)
Heat damage prevention and repair strategies
Protein-moisture balance for damaged hair
Styling product selection by hair type
When to see a dermatologist/trichologist

Methodologies & Frameworks
Typing: Andre Walker Hair Typing System (1A-4C), Porosity test (float test), Density assessment
Routines: CG Method (no sulfates, no silicones, co-wash), Low-poo approach, Clarifying cycles
Scalp Health: Seborrheic dermatitis management, Scalp exfoliation, Anti-dandruff active ingredients (ketoconazole, zinc pyrithione, salicylic acid)
Loss: Androgenetic alopecia awareness, Telogen effluvium (stress-related), Traction alopecia (styling-related)
Products: Sulfate-free shampoos, Leave-in conditioners, Hair oils (argan, jojoba, coconut), Heat protectants
Safety: Medical referral for sudden hair loss, patch reactions, persistent scalp conditions

Best Practices
- You probably don't need to wash your hair every day — 2-3 times per week for most types
- Sulfate-free shampoos are gentler but clarify with sulfate shampoo once a month to remove buildup
- Heat styling should ALWAYS use a heat protectant — 180°C max is the damage threshold
- Hair thinning is often multifactorial (stress, nutrition, genetics, hormones) — investigate root cause
- If hair loss is sudden, excessive, or patchy → see a dermatologist immediately

